{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-04",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_04_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "The Black Bird",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 7,
  "page_start_sec": 489.34,
  "page_end_sec": 732.94,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.657,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 489.34,
      "end": 490.66,
      "text": "She jumped up on her feet.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 490.8,
      "end": 492.26,
      "text": "Her face crimsoned"
    },
    {
      "start": 492.54,
      "end": 492.94,
      "text": "painfully,"
    },
    {
      "start": 493.44,
      "end": 495.38,
      "text": "but she held her head erect and she"
    },
    {
      "start": 495.38,
      "end": 496.82,
      "text": "looked Spade straight in the eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 497.8,
      "end": 498.54,
      "text": "\"I deserve that,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 498.66,
      "end": 499.34,
      "text": "she said."
    },
    {
      "start": 499.5,
      "end": 500.58,
      "text": "\"I deserve it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 500.68,
      "end": 500.78,
      "text": "but—"
    },
    {
      "start": 501.18,
      "end": 501.66,
      "text": "oh!—"
    },
    {
      "start": 501.84,
      "end": 504.12,
      "text": "I did want your help so much."
    },
    {
      "start": 504.16,
      "end": 505.56,
      "text": "I do want it, and need"
    },
    {
      "start": 505.56,
      "end": 506.66,
      "text": "it, so much."
    },
    {
      "start": 507.42,
      "end": 509.18,
      "text": "And the lie was in the way I said it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 509.78,
      "end": 511.56,
      "text": "and not at all in what I said.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 512.5,
      "end": 513.18,
      "text": "She turned away,"
    },
    {
      "start": 513.62,
      "end": 515.18,
      "text": "no longer holding herself erect."
    },
    {
      "start": 515.48,
      "end": 518.48,
      "text": "\"It is my own fault that you can't believe me now.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 519.52,
      "end": 520.96,
      "text": "Spade's face reddened",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 520.96,
      "end": 522.28,
      "text": "and he looked down at the floor,"
    },
    {
      "start": 522.34,
      "end": 522.72,
      "text": "muttering:"
    },
    {
      "start": 523.38,
      "end": 523.78,
      "text": "\"Now"
    },
    {
      "start": 524.42,
      "end": 525.38,
      "text": "you are dangerous.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 526.432,
      "end": 529.1,
      "text": "Brigid O'Shaughnessy went to the table and picked up his hat.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 529.98,
      "end": 531.56,
      "text": "She came back and stood in front of him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 531.58,
      "end": 532.3,
      "text": "holding the hat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 532.84,
      "end": 534.0,
      "text": "not offering it to him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 534.12,
      "end": 536.46,
      "text": "but holding it for him to take if he wished."
    },
    {
      "start": 537.44,
      "end": 538.86,
      "text": "Her face was white and thin."
    },
    {
      "start": 540.192,
      "end": 541.8,
      "text": "Spade looked at his hat and asked:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 542.24,
      "end": 543.52,
      "text": "\"What happened last night?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 545.152,
      "end": 546.88,
      "text": "\"Floyd came to the hotel at nine o'clock,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 546.94,
      "end": 548.12,
      "text": "and we went out for a walk."
    },
    {
      "start": 548.76,
      "end": 550.38,
      "text": "I suggested that so Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 550.52,
      "end": 551.62,
      "text": "Archer could see him."
    },
    {
      "start": 551.98,
      "end": 554.4,
      "text": "We stopped at a restaurant in Geary Street,"
    },
    {
      "start": 554.64,
      "end": 555.86,
      "text": "I think it was,"
    },
    {
      "start": 556.08,
      "end": 557.84,
      "text": "for supper and to dance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 558.36,
      "end": 561.52,
      "text": "and came back to the hotel at about half-past twelve."
    },
    {
      "start": 562.784,
      "end": 564.04,
      "text": "Floyd left me at the door,"
    },
    {
      "start": 564.06,
      "end": 565.82,
      "text": "and I stood inside and watched Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 566.04,
      "end": 566.3,
      "text": "Archer"
    },
    {
      "start": 566.3,
      "end": 568.7,
      "text": "follow him down the street, on the other side."
    },
    {
      "start": 569.64,
      "end": 570.0,
      "text": "\"Down?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 570.3,
      "end": 572.22,
      "text": "You mean towards Market Street?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 572.96,
      "end": 573.48,
      "text": "\"Yes.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 574.3,
      "end": 576.72,
      "text": "\"Do you know what they'd be doing in the neighborhood",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 576.72,
      "end": 578.82,
      "text": "of Bush and Stockton, where Archer was shot?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 580.416,
      "end": 582.0,
      "text": "\"Isn't that near where Floyd lived?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 582.98,
      "end": 583.58,
      "text": "\"No.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 583.7,
      "end": 585.9,
      "text": "It would be nearly a dozen blocks out of his"
    },
    {
      "start": 585.9,
      "end": 588.34,
      "text": "way if he was going from your hotel to his."
    },
    {
      "start": 589.06,
      "end": 589.36,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 590.16,
      "end": 591.76,
      "text": "what did you do after they had gone?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 592.96,
      "end": 593.64,
      "text": "\"I went to bed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 594.34,
      "end": 596.0,
      "text": "And this morning when I went out for breakfast"
    },
    {
      "start": 596.08,
      "end": 598.34,
      "text": "I saw the headlines in the papers and read about—"
    },
    {
      "start": 598.54,
      "end": 599.44,
      "text": "you know."
    },
    {
      "start": 600.26,
      "end": 602.04,
      "text": "Then I went up to Union Square,"
    },
    {
      "start": 602.32,
      "end": 604.42,
      "text": "where I had seen automobiles for hire,"
    },
    {
      "start": 605.08,
      "end": 607.32,
      "text": "and got one and went to the hotel for my luggage."
    },
    {
      "start": 608.38,
      "end": 610.58,
      "text": "After I found my room had been searched yesterday"
    },
    {
      "start": 610.8,
      "end": 612.34,
      "text": "I knew I would have to move,"
    },
    {
      "start": 612.96,
      "end": 614.78,
      "text": "and I had found this place yesterday afternoon."
    },
    {
      "start": 615.26,
      "end": 617.76,
      "text": "So I came up here and then telephoned your office.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 619.22,
      "end": 620.06,
      "text": "\"Your room at the St.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 620.18,
      "end": 621.0,
      "text": "Mark was searched?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 621.24,
      "end": 621.92,
      "text": "he asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 623.05,
      "end": 623.4,
      "text": "\"Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 623.4,
      "end": 624.81,
      "text": "while I was at your office.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 625.6,
      "end": 626.28,
      "text": "She bit her lip."
    },
    {
      "start": 627.22,
      "end": 628.34,
      "text": "\"I didn't mean to tell you that.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 629.74,
      "end": 632.3,
      "text": "\"That means I'm not supposed to question you about it?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 633.2,
      "end": 634.28,
      "text": "She nodded shyly.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 634.66,
      "end": 635.54,
      "text": "He frowned.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 636.54,
      "end": 638.24,
      "text": "She moved his hat a little in her hands.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 638.94,
      "end": 640.78,
      "text": "He laughed impatiently and said:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 641.72,
      "end": 643.42,
      "text": "\"Stop waving the hat in my face."
    },
    {
      "start": 644.256,
      "end": 645.96,
      "text": "Haven't I offered to do what I can?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 647.26,
      "end": 648.34,
      "text": "She smiled contritely,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 648.54,
      "end": 650.06,
      "text": "returned the hat to the table,"
    },
    {
      "start": 650.18,
      "end": 652.44,
      "text": "and sat beside him on the settee again."
    },
    {
      "start": 653.42,
      "end": 653.82,
      "text": "He said:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 654.54,
      "end": 656.46,
      "text": "\"I've got nothing against trusting you blindly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 656.96,
      "end": 658.92,
      "text": "except that I won't be able to do you much good"
    },
    {
      "start": 659.32,
      "end": 661.64,
      "text": "if I haven't some idea of what it's all about."
    },
    {
      "start": 661.94,
      "end": 662.86,
      "text": "For instance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 663.31,
      "end": 665.46,
      "text": "I've got to have some sort of a line"
    },
    {
      "start": 665.6,
      "end": 666.9,
      "text": "on your Floyd Thursby.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 667.73,
      "end": 669.08,
      "text": "\"I met him in the Orient.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 669.34,
      "end": 670.2,
      "text": "She spoke slowly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 670.52,
      "end": 672.26,
      "text": "looking down at a pointed finger"
    },
    {
      "start": 672.44,
      "end": 674.46,
      "text": "tracing eights on the settee between them."
    },
    {
      "start": 674.96,
      "end": 677.4,
      "text": "\"We came here from Hongkong last week."
    },
    {
      "start": 678.22,
      "end": 678.54,
      "text": "He was—"
    },
    {
      "start": 678.96,
      "end": 680.52,
      "text": "he had promised to help me."
    },
    {
      "start": 681.5,
      "end": 683.12,
      "text": "He took advantage of my helplessness"
    },
    {
      "start": 683.12,
      "end": 685.06,
      "text": "and dependence on him to betray me.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 686.08,
      "end": 686.68,
      "text": "\"Betray you how?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 688.1,
      "end": 689.48,
      "text": "She shook her head and said nothing.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 690.14,
      "end": 690.98,
      "text": "Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 691.02,
      "end": 692.18,
      "text": "frowning with impatience,"
    },
    {
      "start": 692.24,
      "end": 692.58,
      "text": "asked:"
    },
    {
      "start": 693.14,
      "end": 694.78,
      "text": "\"Why did you want him shadowed?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 696.16,
      "end": 698.04,
      "text": "\"I wanted to learn how far he had gone.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 698.56,
      "end": 700.76,
      "text": "He wouldn't even let me know where he was staying."
    },
    {
      "start": 701.7,
      "end": 703.36,
      "text": "I wanted to find out what he was doing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 704.1,
      "end": 704.86,
      "text": "whom he was meeting,"
    },
    {
      "start": 705.06,
      "end": 705.94,
      "text": "things like that.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 707.28,
      "end": 708.12,
      "text": "\"Did he kill Archer?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 709.38,
      "end": 710.3,
      "text": "She looked up at him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 710.4,
      "end": 710.84,
      "text": "surprised."
    },
    {
      "start": 711.78,
      "end": 712.3,
      "text": "\"Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 712.3,
      "end": 712.7,
      "text": "certainly,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 713.32,
      "end": 713.68,
      "text": "she said."
    },
    {
      "start": 714.18,
      "end": 716.52,
      "text": "\"He had a Luger in a shoulder-holster.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 717.056,
      "end": 718.48,
      "text": "Archer wasn't shot with a Luger.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 719.26,
      "end": 721.64,
      "text": "\"He had a revolver in his overcoat-pocket,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 721.82,
      "end": 722.24,
      "text": "she said."
    },
    {
      "start": 723.02,
      "end": 723.7,
      "text": "\"You saw it?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 724.44,
      "end": 724.76,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 724.84,
      "end": 725.78,
      "text": "I've seen it often."
    },
    {
      "start": 726.56,
      "end": 728.22,
      "text": "I know he always carries one there."
    },
    {
      "start": 729.1,
      "end": 730.26,
      "text": "I didn't see it last night,"
    },
    {
      "start": 730.7,
      "end": 732.94,
      "text": "but I know he never wears an overcoat without it.\""
    }
  ]
}